# Webview UI design policy

New and updated UI in `src/webview/` must match the Coop design system in `src/webview/globals.css`. Do **not** introduce one-off modals, VS Code validation boxes, or raw `style={{ background: var(--vscode-button-...) }}` unless there is no existing pattern.

## Tokens (prefer CSS variables)

- Surfaces: `--coop-panel-canvas`, `--coop-composer-surface`, `--coop-settings-card`, `--coop-pill-surface`
- Text: `--coop-panel-foreground`, `--coop-panel-muted`, `--coop-composer-text`
- Borders: `--coop-composer-border`, `--coop-settings-divider`, `--coop-pill-border`

## Layout shell

- Root panels: `coop-panel coop-canvas-bg`
- Settings-style pages: `coop-settings-shell`, `coop-settings-header`, `coop-settings-body`, `coop-settings-card`

## Modals & overlays

- Backdrop + dialog: `coop-prompt-modal-backdrop` → `coop-prompt-modal`
- Header: `coop-prompt-modal-header`, `coop-prompt-modal-title`, close via `coop-icon-btn` + SVG (see `PromptLibraryModal.tsx`)
- Body scroll: `coop-prompt-modal-scroll`
- Section labels: `coop-prompt-modal-section-title`, body copy: `coop-prompt-modal-muted` / `coop-prompt-modal-note`
- Footer actions: `coop-prompt-modal-footer` + `coop-settings-action-btn`
- Escape to close; backdrop click closes

## Controls

- Primary/secondary actions: `coop-settings-action-btn` (not raw VS Code button vars)
- Text actions: `coop-text-btn`
- Icon buttons: `coop-icon-btn`
- Toggle rows: `coop-settings-checkbox-row`, `coop-settings-row-title`, `coop-settings-row-desc`
- Header chips/pills: `coop-quick-action-pill` + `coop-quick-action-status-dot`
- Top-bar toggles (on/off): `coop-autocomplete-control` pattern (`AutocompleteStatus.tsx`)

## Lists & status

- Integration/repo rows: `coop-health-integration`, `coop-health-integration-name`, `coop-health-integration-meta`
- Status chips: `coop-health-status` (+ `--healthy` / `--degraded` / `--offline` when applicable)
- Inline errors: `coop-settings-test-message--error`

## Integration result cards

Quick-action and multi-source outputs (Find Owner, Trace Decision, Jira/Teams/Slack sections, source conflicts) use the shared shell in `src/webview/components/IntegrationResultCard.tsx` and `coop-result-*` classes in `globals.css`.

- Card shell: `IntegrationResultCard` + `IntegrationResultStack`
- Sections: `IntegrationResultSection`, `IntegrationResultRow`, `IntegrationResultCollapsible`
- Chips / nested blocks: `IntegrationResultBadge`, `IntegrationResultNested`, `IntegrationResultCode`
- Actions: `coop-settings-action-btn`, `coop-text-btn` (not raw `vscode-button-*`)

Do **not** use `vscode-editorWidget-background`, heavy `border-b` stacks, or uppercase section labels on new integration output UI.

## Reference implementations

- Modal: `src/webview/components/PromptLibraryModal.tsx`
- Settings sections: `src/webview/components/SettingsPanel.tsx`
- Integration results: `src/webview/OwnershipCard.tsx`, `src/webview/DecisionTimeline.tsx`
- Explorer overlay: `src/webview/RemoteExplorer.tsx`
- Context mode: `src/webview/LightningModePanel.tsx`

Before adding new CSS classes, check if an existing `coop-*` class in `globals.css` already fits.
